      "id": "8eefa2fc_dc8b990a",
      "file_path": "runtime-controlloop/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/runtime/supervision/comm/ControlLoopUpdatePublisher.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 78,
      "message": "This || is to distinguish that the ControlLoopElement is a PolicyControlLoopElement, It can have either a \"policy-type-id\" or a \"policy-id\". If anything of these exists then, the inner || is to distinguish if we have any new policies or policy-types provided in the service template fragment. I think || works better here rather than && here as it can have either new policy-types or new policies definitions.\n\nDuplicate code is written on the Participant, which is the receiving side of this message in TestListenerUtils to frame a sample ToscaServiceTemplateFragment. Will consolidate these duplications, and move to common and refactor the same in Jakarata as part of https://jira.onap.org/browse/POLICY-3540",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7504,
        "name": "Sirisha Manchikanti",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sirisha.manchikanti@est.tech",
        "username": "Sirisha_Manchikanti"
      },
